    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 1062
                    The Secretary of State to the
                        Ambassador in France (
                        Caffery
                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv02</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1062</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1062</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-07-20T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1062" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1062">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of the Army Files: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1062<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJ1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-20">July 20,
                            1945</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Victory1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi>
                    </gloss> 116. For the Ambassador from the Secretary of State.</p>
                <p>I have today<note n="1" xml:id="d1062fn1">i. e., July 19, the date the message
                        was drafted.</note> addressed a letter to <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> proposing Soviet participation in supervising Greek
                    elections along the lines of the text proposed in the Department’s telegram of
                    July 17,<note n="2" xml:id="d1062fn2">
                        <ref target="#d1059">Document No. 1059</ref>.</note> which was repeated to
                    you. I would appreciate your making a similar proposal to the French Government
                    immediately.</p>
                <p>The British Delegation suggests, and I concur, that no publicity whatever be
                    given to this proposal until replies are received from the French and Soviet
                    Governments and the Greek Government can be appropriately informed.</p>
                <p>Sent to Paris. Repeated to Washington and Athens.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
